<TITLE> European shares extend gains as banks rally </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 LONDON, March 12 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - European shares rallied by 2 percent midmorning on Wednesday as a rise in bank shares gained momentum and U.S. stock futures turned positive. Financial shares were the top performers, led by UBS and Credit Suisse which both rose by more than 6 percent following joint action by the world's major central banks on Tuesday to ease strains in the credit markets. By 1013 GMT the FTSEurofirst 300 index of top European shares was up 1.9 percent at 1,293.11 points, having risen by as much as 2.1 percent to a session high of 1,296.05 points. The DJStoxx index of European banking shares was last up 3 percent, compared with a 2 percent gain earlier. US futures were up between 0.3 and 0.4 percent, having reversed earlier losses. Shares on Wall Street rose by more than 3 percent on Tuesday after the Federal Reserve said it was teaming up with other central banks to inject extra cash into the money marke
